leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|paired|process|results|people|vision|Making work hold together|Your gift is turning complexity into a route people can understand, sequence, own, and move through with more reliable progress.|The trap is that the work can become organised before it becomes fully shared, leaving people clear on the plan but less connected to the ownership or purpose behind it.|Keep your structure and delivery discipline, but bring People and Vision in before the route is final, so the work is owned and meaningful as well as clear.|This pattern works best when your Process strength and Results drive operate as one disciplined route. You make complexity more manageable, convert discussion into action, and help work become clearer and more accountable. The development edge is to make sure People and Vision enter early enough that the route is not only efficient, but also shared, purposeful, and easier for others to own.|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::paired
